 'taqueriafundadores.com', 'trevi.it', 'ttsamexico.com', 'vattacademy.com', 'vxcase.com.br', 'zoominfo.com'], 'email-addr': ['info@hostingfest.net', 'strtn14@gmail.com'], 'ipv4-addr': ['64.76.20.226'], 'url': ['http://adensa.tech/', 'http://www.hig.se', 'http://www.linkedin.com/company/hostingfest', 'http://www.sgpbusiness.com/company/Ang-Brothers-Me-Pte-Ltd', 'http://www.zoominfo.com/c/ga%CC%88vle/1142576926', 'http://www.zoominfo.com/c/secretaria-municipal-de-sau%CC%81de-de-fortaleza/431949261', 'http://www.zoominfo.com/c/swiss-rose-factory/481426718', 'https://esusbelacruz.fixtecnologia.com.br/', 'https://hostingfest.net/', 'https://saude.fortaleza.ce.gov.br/', 'https://strtn.org/', 'https://web.archive.org/web/20250815130556/https://hostingfest.net/', 'https://www.hig.se/', 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/hostingfest', 'https://www.sgpbusiness.com/company/Ang-Brothers-Me-Pte-Ltd', 'https://www.zoominfo.com/c/ga%CC%88vle/1142576926', 'https://www.zoominfo.com/c/secretaria-municipal-de-sau%CC%81de-de-fortaleza/431949261', 'https://www.zoominfo.com/c/swiss-rose-factory/481426718']}}, {'title': 'Upgrades MaaS Ecosystem with Modular ToolsInsikt Group identified four new malware families from TAG-195 (Golden Chickens, Venom Spider), a financially motivated malware-as-a-service developer. The families include TinyEgg, a lightweight initial-access backdoor; ChonkyChicken, which expands capabilities with browser credential theft and session automation; a modularized ChonkyChicken variant using controller-and-plugin architecture; and ChromEggscalator, a modified Chrome encryption-bypass tool. TAG-127 has been observed deploying TinyEgg via ClickFix campaigns using fake security verification pages. The modular architecture reduces static detection exposure and enables selective capability provisioning to operators. All families share consistent architectural traits including WebSocket command-and-control, Run key persistence, string obfuscation, and execution via legitimate Windows binaries. This represents a deliberate architectural transition toward operator-driven tooling within the TAG-195 MaaS ecosystem.Pulse ID: 6a6241aa476b940a0df81e20 Pulse Link: https://otx.alienvault.com/pulse/6a6241aa476b940a0df81e20  Pulse Author: AlienVault Created: 2026-07-23 16:30:34Be advised, this data is unverified and should be considered preliminary. Always do further verification.#BackDoor #Browser #Chrome #CyberSecurity #Encryption #GSC #InfoSec #MaaS #Malware #MalwareAsAService #OTX #OpenThreatExchange #RAT #Troll #Venom #Windows #bot #AlienVault', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 24 Jul 2026 00:58:29 +0000', 'source': 'https://social.raytec.co/@techbot/116972017809866878', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['otx.alienvault.com'], 'email-addr': ['techbot@social.raytec.co']}}, {'title': 'ASN: AS48113 Location: Riga, LV Added: 2026-07-22T10:42#shodansafari #infosec', 'publication_date': 'Fri, 24 Jul 2026 00:58:29 +0000', 'source': 'https://infosec.exchange/@shodansafari/116972009166029157', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'autonomous-system': ['AS48113']}}, {'title': 'Operation RoundPress Rolls on with More Half-Click Webmail Zero-DaysTA458, a Russia-aligned espionage group likely linked to GRU, continues exploiting half-click cross-site scripting vulnerabilities in webmail platforms to steal sensitive email data. These exploits require no user interaction beyond opening the malicious email in webmail. The actor exploited multiple zero-days including SOGo (CVE-2026-8496), Zimbra (CVE-2025-27915), and mDaemon (CVE-2025-3929), alongside n-day Roundcube vulnerabilities. TA458 deploys SpyPress malware, an obfuscated JavaScript-based tool customized for each targeted mailserver, stealing credentials, contacts, and emails. The group primarily targets Ukrainian government entities and Eastern European military installations across Albania, Greece, Moldova, and Türkiye, with occasional focus on chemical, telecommunications, and technology sectors. Recent variants include backdoor mechanisms for persistent access through reverse shells and webshells.Pulse ID: 6a6241a95227e5bddd350d13 Pulse Link: https://otx.alienvault.com/pulse/6a6241a95227e5bddd350d13  Pulse Author: AlienVault Created: 2026-07-23 16:30:33Be advised, this data is unverified and should be considered preliminary. Always do further verification.#Albania #BackDoor #CyberSecurity #EasternEurope #Email #Espionage #Europe #Government #InfoSec #Java #JavaScript #Malware #Military #OTX #OpenThreatExchange #RAT #Russia #SMS #Telecom #Telecommunication #UK #Ukr #Ukrainian #Webmail #ZeroDay #Zimbra #bot #AlienVault', 'publication_date': 'Thu, 23 Jul 2026 23:56:59 +0000', 'source': 'https://social.raytec.co/@techbot/116971900572646825', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['otx.alienvault.com'], 'email-addr': ['techbot@social.raytec.co'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2026-8496', 'CVE-2025-27915', 'CVE-2025-3929']}}, {'title': "Email threat landscape: Q2 2026 trends and insightsDuring Q2 2026, Microsoft detected approximately 7.6 billion email-based phishing threats, with monthly volumes declining from 2.7 billion in April to 2.4 billion in June. The quarter was significantly shaped by the downstream effects of Microsoft's Digital Crimes Unit disruption of the Tycoon2FA phishing-as-a-service platform in March, resulting in a 92% decline in associated phishing volume. QR code phishing attacks peaked at 18.7 monthly attacks in March before declining 48% by June, while CAPTCHA-gated phishing fell 81% from its March high. Credential phishing remained the dominant objective, accounting for 94-96% of all payload-based attacks. Business email compromise activity returned to historical norms after an anomalous April surge. Microsoft Teams-based threats grew substantially, with weekly malicious call attempts reaching nearly ten times the mid-2025 baseline by quarter end.Pulse ID: 6a6241aa79fc3235d84045f9 Pulse Link: https://otx.alienvault.com/pulse/6a6241aa79fc3235d84045f9  Pulse Author: AlienVault Created: 2026-07-23 16:30:34Be advised, this data is unverified and should be considered preliminary. Always do further verification.#2FA #CAPTCHA #CyberSecurity #Email #InfoSec #Microsoft #MicrosoftTeams #OTX #OpenThreatExchange #Phishing #bot #AlienVault", 'publication_date': 'Thu, 23 Jul 2026 23:56:59 +0000', 'source': 'https://social.raytec.co/@techbot/116971900449014162', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['otx.alienvault.com'], 'email-addr': ['techbot@social.raytec.co']}}, {'title': 'Possible Phishing 🎣  on: ⚠️hxxps[:]//new[.]express[.]adobe[.]com/webpage/E9lDLe8tKruFv  🧬 Analysis at: https://urldna.io/scan/6a6280eb3b7750000452976f #cybersecurity #phishing #infosec #urldna #scam #infosec', 'publication_date': 'Thu, 23 Jul 2026 23:56:59 +0000', 'source': 'https://infosec.exchange/@urldna/116971890994439598', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'artifact': [], 'autonomous-system': [], 'directory': [], 'domain-name': [], 'email-addr': [], 'email-message': [], 'file': [], 'ipv4-addr': [], 'ipv6-addr': [], 'mac-addr': [], 'mutex': [], 'network-traffic': [], 'process': [], 'software': [], 'url': [], 'user-account': [], 'windows-registry-key': [], 'x509-certificate': [], 'vulnerability': [], 'mitre': []}}, {'title': '"Just self-host" is advice for about five percent of people and a fantasy for the rest. I run infrastructure for a living. I still don\'t self-host my own email. The real move usually isn\'t leaving. It\'s picking a better vendor for the spot you\'re in. #DataSovereignty #Privacy #SelfHosted #TechLeadership #InfoSec', 'publication_date': 'Thu, 23 Jul 2026 23:56:59 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.social/@SargentJamesA/116971815608095216', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'email-a